# Customer Churn Prediction & Lifetime Value (LTV) Engine

## Project Summary

Customer retention is one of the most critical challenges faced by telecommunications and subscription-based businesses. Acquiring new customers is significantly more expensive than retaining existing ones, making customer churn prediction an important business problem.

The **Customer Churn Prediction & Lifetime Value (LTV) Engine** is an end-to-end data analytics and machine learning project developed to predict customer churn, estimate Customer Lifetime Value (LTV), and provide actionable business insights. The project combines data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), machine learning, and interactive dashboard visualization to support data-driven business decisions.

Using historical customer data, the system identifies customers who are at high risk of leaving the company and estimates their future business value. These insights help organizations improve customer retention strategies, optimize marketing campaigns, and increase overall profitability.


# Business Problem

Telecommunication companies experience customer loss due to contract changes, pricing, service quality, and customer satisfaction issues. Without identifying customers who are likely to leave, businesses lose significant revenue every year.

This project helps businesses answer important questions such as:

- Which customers are most likely to churn?
- Which customer attributes influence churn the most?
- Which customers have the highest lifetime value?
- How can customer retention strategies be improved using data?


# Project Objectives

The primary objectives of this project are:

- Clean and preprocess customer data
- Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Identify important factors contributing to customer churn
- Build machine learning models to predict churn
- Estimate Customer Lifetime Value (LTV)
- Visualize business insights using interactive dashboards
- Support data-driven customer retention strategies


