# Project Workflow

The project was completed through the following stages:

### 1. Data Collection

Imported the IBM Telco Customer Churn dataset for analysis.

### 2. Data Cleaning

- Removed duplicate records
- Handled missing values
- Converted incorrect data types
- Treated inconsistent values
- Prepared clean data for analysis

### 3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Performed detailed data analysis to identify customer behaviour and business patterns through different visualizations.

Analysis included:

- Churn Distribution
- Contract Analysis
- Internet Service Analysis
- Payment Method Analysis
- Monthly Charges Distribution
- Customer Segmentation
- Correlation Analysis

### 4. Feature Engineering

Prepared features for machine learning by:

- Encoding categorical variables
- Feature scaling
- Creating meaningful variables
- Selecting important features

### 5. Machine Learning

Developed classification models to predict customer churn.

Models evaluated include:

- Logistic Regression
- Random Forest
- XGBoost

Performance was evaluated using:

- Accuracy
- Precision
- Recall
- F1 Score
- ROC-AUC

### 6. Customer Lifetime Value (LTV)

Estimated the future value of customers based on spending behaviour and churn probability.

### 7. Dashboard Development

Created interactive dashboards using Metabase for business users to monitor customer churn and business performance.

